{{Nihongo foot|'''''4 Nin Uchi Mahjong'''''|４人打ち麻雀|4 Nin Uchi Mahjong|group=lower-alpha|extra=lit. "Four Player Strike Mahjong"|lead=yes}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kurx.net/game/gamebook/fc/JPnesHe.txt |title=Japanese title |publisher=JPNES |access-date=2010-05-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100606080547/http://kurx.net/game/gamebook/fc/JPnesHe.txt |archive-date=6 June 2010 |url-status=dead}}</ref> is a 1984 [[mahjong]] [[video game]] developed by [[Hudson Soft]] and published by [[Nintendo]] for the [[Famicom]]. It was released exclusively in [[Japan]]. It is the second mahjong game published by Nintendo.

== Gameplay ==
[[File:4 Nin Uchi Mahjong screenshot.png|thumb|left|The typical initial setup]]
The game consists of [[Japanese mahjong]] (also known as ''riichi'' mahjong) against one to three computer opponents. Spreading to most mahjong-related video games after this one, it has become the most widely accepted form of mahjong to the Japanese gamer.{{citation needed|date=December 2022}} The "[[tile]]s remaining counter" served as a reminder to players about the status of the wall.

